{"uuid":"9e10dae9-cc37-45b4-b141-fbbef5a78304","name":"Understanding tools and their definition","summary":"","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","created_at":"2026-06-20T05:52:57.856410Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T05:55:25.083288Z","settings":{"enabled_web_search":true,"enabled_monkeys_in_a_barrel":true,"tool_search_mode":"auto","preview_feature_uses_artifacts":true,"enabled_artifacts_attachments":false,"enabled_turmeric":true,"thinking_mode":"off","effort_level":"high"},"is_starred":false,"is_temporary":false,"platform":"CLAUDE_AI","is_wiggle_enabled":true,"effective_thinking_mode":"off","current_leaf_message_uuid":"019ee398-f533-7c0a-8ded-897778c6c289","chat_messages":[{"uuid":"019ee396-e3b4-75b9-af71-e617ec25b7c8","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:52:59.001938Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:52:59.001938Z","type":"text","text":"What is a 'Tool' ?","citations":[]}],"sender":"human","index":0,"created_at":"2026-06-20T05:52:59.005273Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T05:52:59.005273Z","truncated":false,"attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000000"},{"uuid":"019ee396-e3b5-78ac-b0eb-0398407ce860","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:52:58.994621Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:53:03.781585Z","type":"text","text":"A **tool** is a capability given to an AI model that lets it perform actions beyond just generating text.\n\nBy default, a language model can only read input and produce text output. Tools extend this by letting the model interact with the outside world — things like:\n\n- **Searching the web** for current information\n- **Running code** to do calculations or process data\n- **Reading/writing files**\n- **Calling APIs** to get data or trigger actions in other services\n- **Querying databases**\n\nThe model decides when to use a tool based on what the user needs, calls it with the right inputs, and then uses the result to form its response.\n\nIn the context of our conversation right now, I have tools like web search, image search, weather lookup, sports data, and others — which is how I can answer questions about current events or show you maps, for example.\n\nIs there a specific context you're asking about — like AI tools, software tools, or something else?","citations":[]}],"sender":"assistant","index":1,"created_at":"2026-06-20T05:53:03.814679Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T05:53:03.814679Z","truncated":false,"stop_reason":"end_turn","attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"019ee396-e3b4-75b9-af71-e617ec25b7c8"},{"uuid":"019ee397-cc67-7415-92e3-99c6c73687fa","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:53:58.453465Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:53:58.453465Z","type":"text","text":"A physical tool","citations":[]}],"sender":"human","index":2,"created_at":"2026-06-20T05:53:58.456645Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T05:53:58.456645Z","truncated":false,"attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"019ee396-e3b5-78ac-b0eb-0398407ce860"},{"uuid":"019ee397-cc67-7df2-bd09-aabeeaac165b","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:53:58.444896Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:54:04.157530Z","type":"text","text":"A **physical tool** is any handheld or mechanical device used to perform a specific task, typically to make work easier or more precise.\n\n## Basic Idea\nTools extend human capability — they let you apply more force, work with greater accuracy, or do things your hands alone can't do.\n\n## Common Categories\n\n- **Cutting tools** — knives, saws, scissors, chisels\n- **Striking tools** — hammers, mallets, sledgehammers\n- **Fastening tools** — screwdrivers, wrenches, pliers\n- **Measuring tools** — rulers, calipers, levels, tape measures\n- **Gripping tools** — clamps, vises, tongs\n- **Shaping tools** — files, sandpaper, planes\n- **Power tools** — drills, angle grinders, jigsaws\n\n## What Makes Something a Tool?\nA tool generally has three qualities:\n1. **It's held or operated by a person** (or a machine)\n2. **It has a specific function** — designed for a particular kind of work\n3. **It amplifies effort** — making a task faster, easier, or possible at all\n\n## A Bit of History\nTools are one of the oldest human inventions. Stone tools date back **over 3 million years**, making tool use a defining characteristic of human (and some pre-human) evolution. Even some animals — like crows and chimpanzees — use simple tools.\n\nWould you like to know more about a specific type of tool?","citations":[]}],"sender":"assistant","index":3,"created_at":"2026-06-20T05:54:04.194985Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T05:54:04.194985Z","truncated":false,"stop_reason":"end_turn","attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"019ee397-cc67-7415-92e3-99c6c73687fa"},{"uuid":"019ee398-f533-7f50-aa07-783c969af952","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:55:14.581268Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:55:14.581268Z","type":"text","text":"Tell me more about 'Vises'.","citations":[]}],"sender":"human","index":4,"created_at":"2026-06-20T05:55:14.584286Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T05:55:14.584286Z","truncated":false,"attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"019ee397-cc67-7df2-bd09-aabeeaac165b"},{"uuid":"019ee398-f533-7c0a-8ded-897778c6c289","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:55:14.571612Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:55:15.842376Z","type":"text","text":"A **vise** (also spelled *vice* in British English) is a mechanical device used to **grip and hold a workpiece securely** in place, freeing up both hands to work on it.","citations":[]},{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:55:15.843194Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:55:15.961080Z","type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019yoiCEnyjmsDWfX8EiBtAz","name":"image_search","input":{"query":"bench vise workshop tool","max_results":3},"message":"Searching for images"},{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T05:55:16.548180Z","stop_timestamp":"2026